<section id="kickstart"
         xreflabel="kickstart">
  <title>
  Kickstart
  </title>

  <section>
    <title>
    Definition
    </title>

    <para>
    Specifies a <varname>PATH</varname> to a kickstart file for inclusion in
    the distribution.  The file is renamed, if needed, to 
    <filename>ks.cfg</filename> and included in the distribution's 
    <filename>os</filename> folder, e.g. 
    <filename>http://server.company.com/distributions/samba-server-5-i386/os/ks.cfg</filename>. 
    This makes the file easy to identify later when someone, possibly someone
    other than the person who built the system distribution, configures 
    network boot (PXE) or virtual machine installations. 
    </para>

   <para>
    The kickstart file is also included in the 
    <emphasis role="strong"><xref linkend="bootiso" /></emphasis> and
    <emphasis role="strong"><xref linkend="diskboot-image" /></emphasis>
    images, and in all 
    <emphasis role="strong"><xref linkend="iso" /></emphasis> images. 
    It will be used automatically when these images are used for new system
    installations.</para> 

    <para>
    This module is a member of the <emphasis role="strong">installer</emphasis>
    module group.
    </para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Syntax
    </title>

    <programlisting>
[&lt;kickstart [enabled=BOOLEAN]&gt;PATH&lt;/kickstart&gt;]
    </programlisting>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Attributes
    </title>

    <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
      enabled
      </term>

      <listitem>
      <para>
      See Common Attribute <emphasis><xref linkend="enabled" /></emphasis>.
      </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Examples
    </title>

    <informalexample>
    <programlisting>
&lt;kickstart&gt;ks.cfg&lt;/kickstart&gt;
    </programlisting>
    </informalexample>
  </section>

